## Background

https://github.com/ImagingDataCommons/libdicom/issues/88

Discussion on openslide, with comments by dclunie

https://github.com/openslide/openslide/issues/511#issuecomment-1774220332

Sample java code for this:

http://www.dclunie.com/pixelmed/software/javadoc/com/pixelmed/apps/MergeConcatenationInstances.html

## What happens now

we read tiles with

	decode_frame(l->file, tile_col, tile_row,
	      buf, l->base.tile_w, l->base.tile_h, &tmp_err))

l is a dicom_level, it contains a single dicom_file->file field, and that
contains the libdicom DcmFilehandle

we then call dcm_filehandle_read_frame_position() which uses
filehandle->frame_index[] (for sparse images) to find the frame number, then 
filehandle->offset_table[] to get the position to read from

## Proposal

dicom_level needs file_index[num_tiles], with each entry pointing to a
dicom_file

need a separate table of all the dicom_file so we can free them ... how are
they freed now?

	dicom_file_destroy() is called when struct associated or struct
	dicom_level are destroyed

	level_destroy() is called in a loop from osr->levels[] in 
	osr destroy

during directory scan, load each DICOM, scan the available tiles, and fill out
the file_index[] array

1. Add osr->files[] array of dicom_file, and destroy in 

	static void destroy(openslide_t *osr) {}

	needs to be g_ptr_array, eg. 

	  g_autoptr(GPtrArray) files =
	    g_ptr_array_new_full(10, (GDestroyNotify) dicom_file_destroy);

2. Add dicom_level->file_index[num_tiles], destroy in level_destroy

3. in dicom_open(), 

